HEADWORD: Sphaeridium
<hw>Sphae*rid"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Sphaeridia</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/ a sphere.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A peculiar
sense organ found upon the exterior of most kinds of sea urchins, and
consisting of an oval or spherical head surmounting a short pedicel. It
is generally supposed to be an olfactory organ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

